## Slide 19 – ePPM stage-gates · how a project travels 🚂

**Layout suggestion:** Horizontal stage-gate diagram (G0 → G6).

**Key points:**
- **ePPM** = Enterprise Project Portfolio Management (system of record)
- **Stage gates:**
  - **G0** – Demand qualification (idea + initial business case)
  - **G3** – Business Case approval (full funding decision; ROLES MUST BE FINAL)
  - **G4 → G5** – Build & Deployment readiness
  - **G6** – Closure (benefits realization handover)
- Every project has an ePPM record updated **monthly** with cost, benefits, schedule, BAU, objectives
- **FPM and ITPM collaborate at every gate**

**Speaker notes:**
Every PMI Tech project lives in ePPM. The stage-gate discipline protects investments and benefits. The most important gate is **G3** – this is where the business case is approved and the project formally exists. After G3, ITPM owns execution and FPM owns benefits realization.

**Visual suggestions:**
- Stage-gate diagram G0 → G6
- Annotate G3 with \"ROLES MUST BE FINAL\"

